<section class="section section--alt" id="kitchen-sink-e2-glossary-clarify">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">A common confusion</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Book balance vs. bank balance.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose"><p>They rarely match to the penny on any given day &mdash; and that is normal. The <strong>book balance</strong> reflects everything you have recorded; the <strong>bank balance</strong> reflects only what has actually cleared the bank. The gap between them is the timing differences: outstanding checks and deposits in transit. Reconciliation does not force the two equal &mdash; it explains the gap, line by line, until nothing is unaccounted for.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

